WEBVTT

00:03.210 --> 00:04.380
Reese: People always think

00:04.380 --> 00:07.210
they understand
how the world works.

00:07.210 --> 00:10.830
♪♪

00:10.830 --> 00:12.380
But we don't really know
anything.

00:12.380 --> 00:14.210
[ Sheep bleating ]

00:14.210 --> 00:16.040
♪♪

00:16.040 --> 00:17.380
We're always asking

00:17.380 --> 00:21.080
if we're alone
in the universe...

00:21.080 --> 00:22.670
if there's something else
out there.

00:22.670 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:28.540
It's the wrong question.

00:28.540 --> 00:33.040
We don't really need to know
what's out there.

00:33.040 --> 00:36.830
We want to know
why we're even here...

00:36.830 --> 00:40.710
and if what we do really...
matters.

00:40.710 --> 00:50.330
♪♪

00:50.330 --> 00:52.920
[ Car door closes ]
Ah! [ Laughs ]

00:52.920 --> 00:54.920
Hey.

00:54.920 --> 00:56.290
Hi.

00:56.290 --> 00:57.330
[ Exhales sharply ]

00:58.620 --> 00:59.750
How are you?

00:59.750 --> 01:01.920
Uh...

01:01.920 --> 01:04.170
[ Gasps ] You look bad.

01:04.170 --> 01:05.670
Oh. Okay.

01:05.670 --> 01:07.000
Um --
Okay.

01:07.000 --> 01:09.580
Well, come on.
Come in.
[ Clears throat ]

01:09.580 --> 01:12.670
Amy: Hey, Reese,
say hi to your Uncle Kevin.

01:12.670 --> 01:15.790
I'm gonna figure out
the food situation.

01:15.790 --> 01:18.500
Hey.
Hey.

01:18.500 --> 01:19.830
What are you listening to?

01:19.830 --> 01:21.000
You wouldn't know them.

01:21.000 --> 01:23.080
Amy: Have you seen
this new math?

01:23.080 --> 01:24.120
I'm an engineering professor,

01:24.120 --> 01:25.710
and I can't even
figure it out.

01:25.710 --> 01:26.750
[ Chuckles ]
Oh.

01:26.750 --> 01:27.920
Maybe you can.

01:27.920 --> 01:29.460
He wouldn't get it.

01:29.460 --> 01:31.000
Well, Reese,
you're probably right.

01:31.000 --> 01:32.380
[ Laughs ]

01:32.380 --> 01:35.420
All right, so we have
meat loaf or chicken.

01:35.420 --> 01:36.540
You know what?

01:36.540 --> 01:38.380
I think I am just going
to get settled

01:38.380 --> 01:40.500
and...hit the sack.

01:40.500 --> 01:43.000
Okay.

01:43.000 --> 01:44.960
Uh...wrong, wrong,
and wrong.

01:44.960 --> 01:47.670
Just -- Okay. Night.

01:49.620 --> 01:51.000
Hey, um, look,

01:51.000 --> 01:53.710
I know that he hasn't been
in our lives lately,

01:53.710 --> 01:54.830
but he needs us.

01:54.830 --> 01:57.290
Give him a chance.

01:57.290 --> 02:01.330
[ Music plays over earbuds ]

02:01.330 --> 02:04.580
[ Insects chirping
in distance ]

02:04.580 --> 02:06.210
Amy:
That's a new mattress.

02:06.210 --> 02:08.330
Oh, you didn't
have to do that.

02:08.330 --> 02:10.290
Well, the old one was,
like, 20 years old,

02:10.290 --> 02:12.170
so I think, legally,
actually I did.

02:12.170 --> 02:13.750
[ Chuckling ]

02:13.750 --> 02:15.790
And if your girlfriend
wants to come visit,

02:15.790 --> 02:16.710
we have plenty of rooms.

02:16.710 --> 02:18.580
Yeah. No. Um...

02:18.580 --> 02:19.710
That's kind of over.

02:19.710 --> 02:21.380
[ Sighs ]
Oh.

02:21.380 --> 02:22.790
Sorry to hear that.

02:22.790 --> 02:23.790
Oh, it's not a big deal.

02:23.790 --> 02:27.170
How's, um...work?

02:27.170 --> 02:28.420
Fine.

02:28.420 --> 02:29.500
It's great.

02:29.500 --> 02:33.000
Um...got tenure,
so, full professor.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.920
[ Chuckles ]
So, yeah.

02:34.920 --> 02:36.500
Nice.

02:36.500 --> 02:38.710
Awesome.

02:38.710 --> 02:39.750
I missed you.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.120
You know,
if you ever want to --

02:42.120 --> 02:43.500
Reese hit maximum teenager,
huh?

02:43.500 --> 02:45.290
Oh. Yeah.

02:45.290 --> 02:47.420
Well, she's just
trying to be cool

02:47.420 --> 02:48.790
in front of you.
Ah.

02:48.790 --> 02:50.080
She's been going through
some stuff

02:50.080 --> 02:51.710
since Jon died.

02:51.710 --> 02:54.210
♪♪

02:54.210 --> 02:57.210
Yeah, um...

02:57.210 --> 03:00.170
sorry I haven't been,
you know, around.

03:00.170 --> 03:01.920
It's okay.

03:01.920 --> 03:04.330
We're okay.

03:04.330 --> 03:06.790
Except she won't
talk about him at all --

03:06.790 --> 03:09.920
to me, to anyone.

03:09.920 --> 03:11.460
She doesn't see her friends.

03:11.460 --> 03:12.580
She doesn't really do
much of anything.

03:12.580 --> 03:13.710
She's just kind of
pulled out of her life.

03:13.710 --> 03:15.120
I'm...

03:15.120 --> 03:16.670
I'm worried about her.

03:16.670 --> 03:18.790
Sure.
She used to love
playing soccer,

03:18.790 --> 03:20.330
and then she quit the team.

03:20.330 --> 03:21.750
I keep hounding her
to play again, but --

03:21.750 --> 03:23.000
I just --
I feel like it would help.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.000
[ Chuckles ]

03:24.000 --> 03:26.120
♪♪

03:26.120 --> 03:26.960
Sorry.

03:26.960 --> 03:29.580
I'm just unloading on you.

03:29.580 --> 03:30.960
No, it's fine.

03:30.960 --> 03:31.750
[ Sighs ]
It's fine.

03:31.750 --> 03:35.960
♪♪

03:35.960 --> 03:37.420
I'm glad you're here.

03:37.420 --> 03:40.830
♪♪

03:40.830 --> 03:42.670
You can stay
as long as you like.

03:42.670 --> 03:44.040
Yeah -- probably just
a couple days.

03:44.040 --> 03:45.250
[ Clears throat ]

03:45.250 --> 03:46.670
♪♪

03:46.670 --> 03:48.380
Okay.

03:48.380 --> 03:49.710
♪♪

03:49.710 --> 03:50.710
[ Sighs ]

03:50.710 --> 03:52.250
♪♪

03:52.250 --> 03:56.500
[ Insects chirping ]

03:56.500 --> 03:58.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:58.880 --> 04:01.790
[ Rumbling in distance ]

04:01.790 --> 04:06.420
[ Glass rattling ]

04:06.420 --> 04:07.750
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:07.750 --> 04:10.790
[ Rumbling,
glass rattling continues ]

04:10.790 --> 04:11.960
Aah! [ Groans ]

04:11.960 --> 04:14.040
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

04:21.040 --> 04:22.460
We need you
to come with us!

04:22.460 --> 04:24.500
Me?

04:24.500 --> 04:25.920
No, idiot, me!

04:25.920 --> 04:27.250
Watch Reese for me!

04:27.250 --> 04:28.960
I'll call you
as soon as I can!

04:28.960 --> 04:31.670
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

04:31.670 --> 04:33.670
Um...

04:33.670 --> 04:34.880
Okay...

04:37.210 --> 04:38.460
Okay, well, I'll just --

04:38.460 --> 04:40.250
You know, I'll be here!

04:40.250 --> 04:41.790
I'm just gonna
lock the door?!

04:41.790 --> 04:43.880
Okay, cool.

04:43.880 --> 04:50.380
[ Insects chirping ]

04:50.380 --> 04:52.580
Does that kind of thing
happen a lot?

04:52.580 --> 04:53.790
Nope.

04:55.830 --> 05:01.580
Um...maybe you should
go back to sleep.

05:01.580 --> 05:02.960
When I feel like it.

05:06.120 --> 05:07.080
What are you reading?

05:08.460 --> 05:10.960
Mystery? Humor?

05:10.960 --> 05:12.080
Self-help?

05:12.080 --> 05:14.210
Romance?

05:14.210 --> 05:16.040
Y-A?

05:16.040 --> 05:17.290
I got some ideas
for a Y-A novel.

05:17.290 --> 05:19.500
Can you please
just go away?

05:19.500 --> 05:20.790
Serious question --

05:20.790 --> 05:23.170
Would you rather read a book
called "Vampire Sluts"

05:23.170 --> 05:24.920
or "Murder Teens"
or "Robot High School"?

05:24.920 --> 05:26.420
What is your problem?

05:26.420 --> 05:28.330
'Cause I'm leaning towards
"Vampire Sluts."

05:28.330 --> 05:30.880
Why are you even here?
[ Clears throat ]

05:30.880 --> 05:34.540
Your mom insisted.

05:34.540 --> 05:36.750
Because you tried
to kill yourself?

05:39.080 --> 05:40.710
Yep.

05:40.710 --> 05:42.000
Didn't -- didn't take.

05:44.750 --> 05:47.880
But the real question is, um,

05:47.880 --> 05:50.540
why do you think Goth
is still a thing?

05:50.540 --> 05:51.920
I'm not Goth.

05:51.920 --> 05:53.460
Emo.

05:53.460 --> 05:54.710
Do you know
how old you sound right now?

05:54.710 --> 05:55.920
Y-- [Scoffs]

05:55.920 --> 05:59.500
[ Rumbling in distance ]

05:59.500 --> 06:01.170
Um...

06:01.710 --> 06:03.420
W-Why don't you --

06:03.420 --> 06:05.790
Uh, do you want to just
tell me what that was, Reese?

06:05.790 --> 06:07.500
Oh, God.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.380
[ Rumbling continues ]
Look! Look at that!

06:14.670 --> 06:16.210
[ Rumbling stops ]
That was a meteor!

06:16.210 --> 06:17.670
[ Explosion in distance ]
Was that a meteor?

06:17.670 --> 06:19.960
It sure as hell
looked like it.

06:19.960 --> 06:22.210
I mean, your mom
would definitely not want us

06:22.210 --> 06:24.380
to go check that out.
I know.

06:24.380 --> 06:26.380
♪♪

06:26.380 --> 06:27.880
But, I mean,
we're definitely gonna

06:27.880 --> 06:28.960
go check that out, right?

06:28.960 --> 06:32.380
♪♪

06:32.380 --> 06:42.380
♪♪

06:42.380 --> 06:52.380
♪♪

06:52.380 --> 06:56.290
♪♪

06:56.290 --> 06:58.210
Kevin:
I can't see anything.

06:58.210 --> 07:00.750
♪♪

07:00.750 --> 07:02.880
Wait, I don't we s--

07:02.880 --> 07:12.420
♪♪

07:12.420 --> 07:15.750
Reese: It just looks like
a regular rock.

07:15.750 --> 07:17.330
I thought it would look
more like a space thing.

07:17.330 --> 07:22.580
♪♪

07:22.580 --> 07:23.540
I wouldn't touch it!

07:23.540 --> 07:31.620
♪♪

07:31.620 --> 07:33.040
[ Explosion ]

07:33.040 --> 07:35.210
[ Kevin screaming ]

07:35.210 --> 07:36.290
[ Thuds ]

07:36.290 --> 07:40.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:40.170 --> 07:43.000
Woman: Transform yourself.

07:43.000 --> 07:44.710
Transform yourself.

07:44.710 --> 07:46.040
Transform yourself.

07:46.040 --> 07:48.960
Transform yourself.

07:48.960 --> 07:51.830
Transform yourself.

07:51.830 --> 07:53.170
Transform yourself.

07:53.170 --> 07:55.040
Reese:
[ Distorted ] Kevin?

07:55.040 --> 07:56.710
[ Normal voice ]
Kevin!

07:56.710 --> 07:58.380
What is wrong with you?

07:59.210 --> 08:00.210
Wait a minute,
wait a minute.

08:00.210 --> 08:02.460
Wha--
How did we get here?

08:02.460 --> 08:05.330
What are you talking about?
You drove!

08:05.330 --> 08:06.290
The car?

08:06.290 --> 08:09.170
Oh, my God.
You are the worst!

08:09.170 --> 08:10.580
Well, just tell me
what happened!

08:10.580 --> 08:11.620
You thought
it was an awesome idea

08:11.620 --> 08:12.830
to touch a space rock,

08:12.830 --> 08:15.500
and then you got, like,
electrocuted or something.

08:15.500 --> 08:17.170
This is so weird.

08:17.170 --> 08:19.290
What are you gonna do with it,
anyway?

08:19.290 --> 08:20.960
With what?
The meteor!

08:20.960 --> 08:22.580
I don't want the meteor.

08:22.580 --> 08:24.420
You brought it back
with us!

08:24.420 --> 08:25.620
What?

08:25.620 --> 08:27.000
♪♪

08:27.000 --> 08:28.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

08:28.620 --> 08:31.790
♪♪

08:31.790 --> 08:33.580
W-Why did I do that?

08:33.580 --> 08:36.420
Because you're
a crazy person!

08:36.420 --> 08:37.670
Well, will you help me?

08:37.670 --> 08:39.040
Reese!

08:39.040 --> 08:40.880
♪♪

08:40.880 --> 08:43.000
[ Car door opens,
door slams in distance ]

08:43.000 --> 08:50.170
♪♪

08:50.170 --> 08:53.420
[ Grunts ]

08:53.420 --> 08:55.960
♪♪

08:55.960 --> 08:57.710
Come on!

08:57.710 --> 08:59.330
[ Gasps ]

08:59.330 --> 09:01.920
♪♪

09:01.920 --> 09:02.670
[ Car door closes ]

09:02.670 --> 09:06.080
♪♪

09:06.080 --> 09:07.210
[ Car alarm chirps ]

09:08.670 --> 09:10.040
O'Donnell: Have you had
a chance to ingest

09:10.040 --> 09:11.040
the material we sent?
[ Door beeps ]

09:11.040 --> 09:13.670
Twice.
Initial impressions?

09:13.670 --> 09:16.330
While I appreciate
the midnight helicopter ride,

09:16.330 --> 09:18.080
I don't really know
why I'm here.

09:18.080 --> 09:20.250
These are meteors,
not weapons.

09:20.250 --> 09:22.290
The trajectories in Indonesia
and Greenland --

09:22.290 --> 09:23.460
Save it for the briefing.
We're about to start.

09:23.460 --> 09:24.420
Who's giving it?

09:24.420 --> 09:25.750
You are.

09:25.750 --> 09:27.500
[ Doors open ]

09:27.500 --> 09:30.580
O'Donnell:
Some of you may know of
Dr. Amy Cabrera

09:30.580 --> 09:32.960
from her work with
the UN inspection team in Iraq.

09:32.960 --> 09:35.250
She's a professor of
aeronautical engineering

09:35.250 --> 09:37.880
and one of the best
weapons analysts out there.

09:37.880 --> 09:39.960
Professor,
tell them what you told me.

09:39.960 --> 09:42.250
♪♪

09:42.250 --> 09:43.670
Ladies and gentlemen, um,
good morning.

09:43.670 --> 09:44.750
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:44.750 --> 09:46.080
Over the last 24 hours,

09:46.080 --> 09:48.210
there have been
35 meteor strikes reported

09:48.210 --> 09:49.330
all over the globe.

09:49.330 --> 09:51.540
While this is highly unusual,

09:51.540 --> 09:54.080
there is no evidence
to suggest that it's a weapon.

09:54.080 --> 09:55.710
There have been
no ballistic missile launches

09:55.710 --> 09:56.580
that have been detected.

09:56.580 --> 09:57.710
The trajectory --

09:57.710 --> 09:58.960
General:
In any given year,

09:58.960 --> 10:00.290
there are
5 to 10 meteor strikes

10:00.290 --> 10:02.080
of this magnitude.

10:02.080 --> 10:05.250
How do you explain
35 in a day?

10:05.250 --> 10:06.540
Well, I can only tell you
what they aren't, General.

10:06.540 --> 10:07.620
O'Donnell:
Here's my problem --

10:07.620 --> 10:09.290
If these are supposed
to be meteors,

10:09.290 --> 10:10.920
they sure as hell
don't act like them.

10:10.920 --> 10:12.000
They don't get picked up
on any telemetry

10:12.000 --> 10:13.330
until they hit
the stratosphere.

10:13.330 --> 10:16.290
Could someone be dropping
projectiles from a satellite?

10:16.290 --> 10:17.920
Kinetic weapons
are theoretical.

10:17.920 --> 10:19.290
This isn't science fiction,
General.

10:19.290 --> 10:20.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:20.920 --> 10:22.380
O'Donnell:
Ladies and gentlemen,

10:22.380 --> 10:26.960
our first confirmed strike
in the United States.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.460
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:28.460 --> 10:30.960
Are these coordinates
correct?
Yeah.

10:30.960 --> 10:32.710
♪♪

10:32.710 --> 10:35.790
[ Insects chirping ]

10:35.790 --> 10:39.880
[ Car rattling ]

10:39.880 --> 10:45.830
[ Car alarm blares ]

10:45.830 --> 10:48.000
[ Exhales sharply ]

10:48.000 --> 10:56.880
[ Car alarm blaring
continues ]

10:56.880 --> 10:58.290
[ Car alarm chirps ]

10:58.290 --> 10:59.330
[ Car alarm shuts off ]

10:59.330 --> 11:05.460
[ Roaring ]

11:05.460 --> 11:07.000
[ Noise stops ]

11:07.000 --> 11:17.000
♪♪

11:17.000 --> 11:22.540
♪♪

11:22.540 --> 11:24.080
[ Groans ]

11:26.830 --> 11:29.120
Do not be afraid.

11:29.120 --> 11:31.380
[ Groans ]
You have been chosen!

11:31.380 --> 11:33.380
Kevin?

11:37.540 --> 11:38.790
♪♪

11:38.790 --> 11:41.080
Woman:
Transform yourself.

11:41.080 --> 11:44.750
♪♪

11:44.750 --> 11:47.120
[ Groans ]

11:47.120 --> 11:49.120
Mm...

11:49.120 --> 11:50.830
♪♪

11:50.830 --> 11:53.380
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

11:58.290 --> 12:00.080
[ Cellphone clicks ]

12:01.040 --> 12:03.040
Ame. What's up?

12:03.040 --> 12:04.670
Amy: Kevin,
where the hell have you been?

12:04.670 --> 12:06.420
I have been calling you
all night.

12:06.420 --> 12:08.040
Oh.

12:08.040 --> 12:10.000
Really?
Look, there are reports
of a meteor strike

12:10.000 --> 12:11.000
close to the house.

12:11.000 --> 12:12.170
Did you see it?

12:12.170 --> 12:16.960
[ Whirring in distance ]

12:16.960 --> 12:18.830
Amy:
Kevin, did you see it?

12:18.830 --> 12:21.920
Um...nope, don't think so.

12:21.920 --> 12:23.710
There's nothing for me
to do here,

12:23.710 --> 12:24.920
so I'm on my way back.

12:24.920 --> 12:26.580
But answer your phone,
okay?

12:26.580 --> 12:27.580
Got it.

12:27.580 --> 12:28.500
Uh, yeah, see ya.

12:31.290 --> 12:34.580
[ Glass clinks,
liquid pours ]

12:34.580 --> 12:37.710
♪♪

12:37.710 --> 12:38.880
[ Clears throat ]

12:38.880 --> 12:40.460
♪♪

12:40.460 --> 12:42.040
Morning, sunshine.

12:42.040 --> 12:43.250
You hungry?

12:43.250 --> 12:44.750
Uh, sorry. Who are you?

12:44.750 --> 12:46.420
Drink this.

12:46.420 --> 12:48.920
It looks disgusting,
but it's good for you.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.330
Um, wait, wait, wait --

12:50.330 --> 12:52.750
Listen, you need to start
eating a healthy breakfast.

12:52.750 --> 12:54.000
Your body's a gift from God.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.500
And let's face it.

12:55.500 --> 12:57.000
You've been treating yours
like a rental car.

12:57.000 --> 12:58.170
Uh, well,
so here's the thing,

12:58.170 --> 12:59.620
this isn't actually
your house.

12:59.620 --> 13:01.710
It isn't your house either,
Kevin.

13:01.710 --> 13:04.170
How'd you --
How did you know m--

13:04.170 --> 13:05.880
Drink.

13:07.710 --> 13:09.290
Mm!

13:09.290 --> 13:10.290
No, no, no.
Listen, listen.

13:10.290 --> 13:11.500
You got to go,
or I'm gonna call the c--

13:11.500 --> 13:13.670
♪♪

13:13.670 --> 13:15.830
This...

13:15.830 --> 13:18.170
This is really delicious.

13:18.170 --> 13:20.500
Good. Enjoy that.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.460
And listen.

13:21.460 --> 13:22.880
I'm here
to tell you something

13:22.880 --> 13:24.960
that I suspect
you already know.

13:24.960 --> 13:26.250
Haven't you always felt

13:26.250 --> 13:28.170
that you had
a higher purpose,

13:28.170 --> 13:30.330
that you were meant
for something greater?

13:30.330 --> 13:31.210
[ Exhales ]

13:31.210 --> 13:32.830
Um...nope.

13:32.830 --> 13:33.920
Can't say that I --

13:35.380 --> 13:36.460
Yeah, no.

13:36.460 --> 13:38.290
All right.

13:38.290 --> 13:39.920
All right, all right.
Fine.

13:39.920 --> 13:41.670
[ Clears throat ]

13:41.670 --> 13:44.250
In every generation
since the dawn of Man,

13:44.250 --> 13:47.120
there are 36 righteous souls
in the world.

13:47.120 --> 13:51.500
And they protect humanity
by merely existing.

13:51.500 --> 13:53.830
Now...

13:53.830 --> 13:54.710
There's only one.

13:54.710 --> 13:56.460
Oh.

13:56.460 --> 13:57.710
Okay.

13:57.710 --> 14:00.330
You, Kevin --

14:00.330 --> 14:02.540
You are the last
of the righteous.

14:02.540 --> 14:05.120
Sure.

14:05.120 --> 14:06.790
Cool.

14:06.790 --> 14:08.420
But you're not alone.

14:08.420 --> 14:10.330
I'm a messenger from God.

14:10.330 --> 14:11.540
Oh, good.

14:11.540 --> 14:12.790
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

14:12.790 --> 14:14.000
Whew!
[ Laughing ]
I know, right?

14:15.080 --> 14:16.620
Yeah,
that all sounds great.

14:16.620 --> 14:18.670
I love it.
Kevin.

14:18.670 --> 14:20.460
No, let's do
all of those things

14:20.460 --> 14:21.580
that you said.

14:21.580 --> 14:23.250
Kevin,
put the knife down.

14:23.250 --> 14:24.210
What are you doing?

14:24.210 --> 14:25.210
Reese, get out of here!

14:25.210 --> 14:26.380
No, you don't!

14:26.380 --> 14:27.920
Y-You stay right there.

14:27.920 --> 14:29.210
Who are you talking to?

14:29.210 --> 14:30.750
She can't see me.
[ Laughs ]

14:30.750 --> 14:32.290
Reese, go!
I'll handle this.

14:32.290 --> 14:33.750
Do n-- You better
stop right now!
I can -- I'll --

14:33.750 --> 14:34.880
Kevin.

14:34.880 --> 14:36.920
♪♪

14:36.920 --> 14:38.670
She can't see me.

14:38.670 --> 14:40.880
Are you telling me that
you don't see anybody else

14:40.880 --> 14:42.120
in this kitchen
right now?

14:42.120 --> 14:43.420
♪♪

14:43.420 --> 14:44.620
What happened
to your face?

14:44.620 --> 14:47.420
[ Winces ]

14:47.420 --> 14:48.920
I need a ride to school.

14:48.920 --> 14:51.170
Just please put clothes on.

14:51.170 --> 14:52.750
I'm -- Oh.

14:52.750 --> 14:54.500
[ Sighs ]

14:54.500 --> 14:55.960
♪♪

14:55.960 --> 14:57.380
Leave the knife.

14:57.380 --> 14:59.880
You look like
a crazy person.

14:59.880 --> 15:02.210
♪♪

15:02.210 --> 15:03.330
♪ Hey ♪

15:03.330 --> 15:08.250
♪♪

15:08.250 --> 15:10.170
Hey, uh,
you can hallucinate

15:10.170 --> 15:11.790
if you've had a concussion,
right?

15:11.790 --> 15:13.620
Like, that's like a...

15:13.620 --> 15:15.880
How would I know?

15:15.880 --> 15:17.330
Well, you have your phone
right in front of you.

15:17.330 --> 15:18.670
You could look it up.

15:18.670 --> 15:22.040
You know, ask somebody
on Snapsnatch or whatever.

15:22.040 --> 15:23.620
♪ Free your soul ♪
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

15:23.620 --> 15:24.960
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

15:24.960 --> 15:27.250
I'm just a little...

15:27.250 --> 15:29.210
Things are a little weird
right now.

15:29.210 --> 15:31.210
What is wrong with you?
Nothing.

15:31.210 --> 15:32.960
Nothing is wrong.
I'm cool.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.540
Let's talk about --
Let's talk about you.

15:34.540 --> 15:36.120
What's up?

15:36.120 --> 15:38.620
Huh? Seriously.

15:38.620 --> 15:39.960
Your mom tells me
that you don't have any friends

15:39.960 --> 15:41.380
or something?
Oh, my God.

15:41.380 --> 15:42.420
What?

15:43.420 --> 15:45.620
Let me give you a little advice
on personal relationships.

15:45.620 --> 15:47.040
Dominate.

15:47.040 --> 15:49.170
Just dominate all day long.

15:49.170 --> 15:50.620
Never show weakness,
never show emotions --

15:50.620 --> 15:51.960
That way
you don't get hurt.

15:51.960 --> 15:53.830
You know, you can just drop me
right here.

15:53.830 --> 15:55.170
We're like a mile away.
What are you talking about?

15:56.670 --> 15:58.040
Oh, what?

15:58.040 --> 15:59.290
You don't want
to be seen with me?

15:59.290 --> 16:01.750
Here's fine.
No, no, no, no.

16:01.750 --> 16:04.460
We are driving all the way
to the front door --

16:04.460 --> 16:06.080
all the way.

16:06.080 --> 16:07.880
[ Sighs ]
'Cause I'm your cool uncle,

16:07.880 --> 16:11.000
and people are gonna want
to see that.

16:11.000 --> 16:11.960
Let's rock out. Okay?

16:11.960 --> 16:13.500
How 'bout this?

16:13.500 --> 16:16.330
♪ This is my fight song ♪
I hate you.

16:16.330 --> 16:18.210
♪ Take back my life song ♪

16:18.210 --> 16:23.000
♪ Prove I'm all right song ♪

16:23.000 --> 16:25.540
♪ My power's turned -- ♪

16:25.540 --> 16:27.960
[ Car horn honks ]

16:27.960 --> 16:29.710
Bye-- [ Sighs ]

16:29.710 --> 16:31.290
[ Exhales sharply ]
[ Indistinct
conversations ]

16:31.290 --> 16:32.460
Okay.

16:34.290 --> 16:35.460
Yvette:
I have a question.
[ Gasps ]

16:35.460 --> 16:37.830
Is it that you don't see
she's hurting,

16:37.830 --> 16:40.330
or is it that you just
don't know what to do?

16:40.330 --> 16:42.330
[ Murmurs ]

16:42.330 --> 16:45.500
♪♪

16:45.500 --> 16:47.540
Kevin!

16:47.540 --> 16:49.120
[ Sighs ]

16:49.120 --> 16:50.710
Kevin: Come on.
Come on. Come on.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.580
You need to calm down.

16:52.580 --> 16:53.670
Hi, is Dr. Sloane
available?

16:53.670 --> 16:54.920
It's Kevin Finn.

16:54.920 --> 16:56.920
Kevin, put the phone away.

16:56.920 --> 16:58.170
Uh...
Oh. He's on a plane.

16:58.170 --> 16:59.880
Um...
can we call the plane?

16:59.880 --> 17:01.750
We do not have time
for this.

17:01.750 --> 17:03.710
Well, I can just talk to you,
right?

17:03.710 --> 17:05.000
You can do that?

17:05.000 --> 17:07.080
Look, I'm a couple blocks away
from a pharmacy.

17:07.080 --> 17:08.920
Can you just call me in
something awesome?

17:08.920 --> 17:10.170
♪ You touch my soul ♪

17:10.170 --> 17:11.500
[ Tires screech ]

17:11.500 --> 17:14.830
♪ She make my heart
stop, drop, and roll ♪

17:14.830 --> 17:18.500
♪ I'm on fire
when you touch my soul ♪

17:18.500 --> 17:20.170
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

17:20.170 --> 17:24.620
♪♪

17:24.620 --> 17:27.620
[ Tires screech ]

17:27.620 --> 17:30.710
♪♪

17:30.710 --> 17:32.290
What the heck
just happened?!

17:32.290 --> 17:35.420
Like I said,
I'm here to protect you.

17:35.420 --> 17:38.210
And that's
what I'm going to do.

17:38.210 --> 17:40.420
So pull your head
out of your ass.

17:40.420 --> 17:41.830
We got work to do.

17:41.830 --> 17:45.290
♪♪

17:49.000 --> 17:50.670
I imagine you have questions.
Go ahead.

17:50.670 --> 17:53.000
[ Inhales sharply ]

17:53.000 --> 17:54.580
You...

17:54.580 --> 17:56.710
threw a truck.

17:56.710 --> 17:57.830
Is that your question?

17:57.830 --> 17:59.670
Maybe?

17:59.670 --> 18:01.580
No! No.

18:02.460 --> 18:03.710
Mm. Are you an angel?

18:03.710 --> 18:05.460
Angels are a human construct.

18:05.460 --> 18:07.710
Let's just say
I'm a warrior for God.

18:07.710 --> 18:09.290
Oh.

18:09.290 --> 18:10.540
Can I see your wings?

18:10.540 --> 18:12.330
Okay, cool,
we're done with questions.

18:12.330 --> 18:14.380
[ Sighs ]
Here's what you need
to understand.

18:14.380 --> 18:15.920
You are the last
of the righteous.

18:15.920 --> 18:18.080
You have a sacred mission

18:18.080 --> 18:19.290
to restore balance
to the world

18:19.290 --> 18:20.880
by anointing 35...
[ Scoffs ] Oh.

18:20.880 --> 18:22.580
...new souls.
[ Sighs ]

18:22.580 --> 18:23.710
Got it?

18:23.710 --> 18:25.710
Got it? Um...

18:25.710 --> 18:26.960
Nope. Nope.

18:26.960 --> 18:28.120
I definitely
don't "got it."

18:28.120 --> 18:31.000
Um, look,
I'm not righteous, okay?

18:31.000 --> 18:32.580
Go down the street
to the church,

18:32.580 --> 18:34.580
I guarantee you'll find
a bunch of people

18:34.580 --> 18:35.880
more righteous than me.

18:35.880 --> 18:37.210
Can't you see the gift
that you've been given?

18:37.210 --> 18:38.620
To serve God, to --
But --

18:38.620 --> 18:40.290
To -- to --
to protect humanity?

18:40.290 --> 18:42.380
What more could one want
from existence?

18:42.380 --> 18:45.670
I can think of millions
of things right now.

18:45.670 --> 18:48.170
Uh, money, naps, girls,

18:48.170 --> 18:50.750
sushi, muscles, uh,
an awesome electric guitar.

18:50.750 --> 18:52.120
Guitar lessons.

18:52.120 --> 18:54.120
[ Groans ]
This is gonna be a problem.

18:54.120 --> 18:55.460
Hey, here's another problem.

18:55.460 --> 18:57.080
I don't believe in God.

18:57.080 --> 18:57.920
Hi.

18:57.920 --> 19:01.500
Uh...I just love this song.

19:01.500 --> 19:03.000
I just don't know
the lyrics.

19:03.000 --> 19:05.330
[ Chuckles ]
'Cause I -- I don't...

19:05.330 --> 19:08.880
God does not stop existing
based on what you believe.

19:08.880 --> 19:10.960
Yeah, well,
I don't believe that, either.

19:10.960 --> 19:12.250
Okay. Well --

19:12.250 --> 19:13.460
Okay.

19:13.460 --> 19:15.880
We need to start building up
your spiritual power

19:15.880 --> 19:17.170
so you can find
the righteous.

19:17.170 --> 19:18.500
That's all. That's all.
Yeah, but you say that --

19:18.500 --> 19:19.750
I don't know what that means,
because --
That's all.

19:19.750 --> 19:21.420
Just trust me!
Tyler:
K-Dog? [ Laughs ]

19:21.420 --> 19:23.330
No way! It's Tyler!

19:23.330 --> 19:24.500
Hey, Ty!

19:24.500 --> 19:25.750
What's going on?

19:25.750 --> 19:27.000
Life, you know?

19:27.000 --> 19:28.830
Been working here
for the past six years --

19:28.830 --> 19:29.830
like, six, seven years.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.170
Great job -- free coffee,

19:31.170 --> 19:33.000
living with my mom, you know,
since the divorce.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.040
Do you remember Tammy?

19:34.040 --> 19:36.460
Oh.
I'm sorry to hear that.

19:36.460 --> 19:39.080
Oh, no. It's all good --
totally amicable.

19:39.080 --> 19:40.170
Oh.
Let's hang out.

19:40.170 --> 19:41.710
I don't have a car
at the moment.

19:41.710 --> 19:42.620
Mine got stolen.

19:42.620 --> 19:43.920
But I've been
biking everywhere,

19:43.920 --> 19:45.080
and it's great.

19:45.080 --> 19:46.000
[ Laughs ]

19:48.750 --> 19:49.710
This shirt...

19:50.710 --> 19:52.830
This is
a really nice shirt.

19:52.830 --> 19:54.250
This is, like,

19:54.250 --> 19:55.790
the nicest shirt
I've ever seen.

19:55.790 --> 19:57.420
[ Sniffs ]
Oh, my God.

19:57.420 --> 19:59.540
Thank you so much
for saying that.

19:59.540 --> 20:00.830
I feel the same way.

20:00.830 --> 20:03.380
I found this shirt
in the street.

20:03.380 --> 20:05.120
It's my favorite
street shirt.

20:05.120 --> 20:06.750
[ Clears throat ]
Sorry.

20:06.750 --> 20:08.000
[ Clears throat ]

20:08.000 --> 20:09.750
K-Dog!

20:09.750 --> 20:11.540
Love this guy!

20:11.540 --> 20:13.330
Yvette: Cute.

20:13.330 --> 20:15.670
You mind explaining to me
what the hell that was?
Why?

20:15.670 --> 20:17.670
That -- that was Tyler.
[ Giggles ] No.

20:17.670 --> 20:19.080
That thing with the shirt.

20:19.080 --> 20:20.540
And with the smoothie.

20:20.540 --> 20:22.790
Okay, what exactly
is the issue?

20:22.790 --> 20:24.120
Uh, well, um...

20:24.120 --> 20:25.080
[ Inhales, clicks tongue ]

20:25.080 --> 20:26.500
I think
everything is beautiful,

20:26.500 --> 20:27.670
and I don't like it.

20:27.670 --> 20:29.250
Oh!

20:29.250 --> 20:31.670
You're seeing the world
through new eyes.

20:31.670 --> 20:32.960
That's a sign.

20:32.960 --> 20:35.460
That's a good sign!
Sign of what?

20:35.460 --> 20:37.750
That you're starting to be
in tune with the Universe.

20:37.750 --> 20:39.830
We need to start
strengthening that today --

20:39.830 --> 20:41.120
quickly.

20:41.120 --> 20:42.830
Fine. How?

20:42.830 --> 20:45.250
By doing something you seem
unaccustomed to, Kevin --

20:45.250 --> 20:47.290
putting others
before yourself, hmm?

20:47.290 --> 20:49.000
Living a life
in service to others...

20:49.000 --> 20:51.290
[ Scoffs ]
...helping those
in need.

20:51.290 --> 20:53.920
I can think of one person
right now in your life

20:53.920 --> 20:55.210
who could use
a little kindness.

20:57.420 --> 20:59.000
Someone close to you.

21:00.790 --> 21:02.830
Someone related to you.

21:02.830 --> 21:04.540
Someone related to me?

21:04.540 --> 21:06.210
Uh...

21:06.210 --> 21:07.670
Your niece.

21:07.670 --> 21:09.330
Reese!

21:09.330 --> 21:10.790
Oh, right. Reese.

21:10.790 --> 21:12.540
Good one. Yep.

21:12.540 --> 21:14.000
[ Sighs ]

21:14.000 --> 21:15.670
This is gonna be harder
than I thought.
Okay.

21:15.670 --> 21:17.000
Kristin: Kevin?

21:18.040 --> 21:21.330
Oh, my God, it is you.

21:21.330 --> 21:22.830
Kristin.

21:22.830 --> 21:24.170
[ Chuckles ]

21:24.170 --> 21:25.080
Wow. Hey.

21:25.080 --> 21:26.170
God, I-I don't think
I've seen you

21:26.170 --> 21:28.080
in, uh, I don't --
10 years?

21:28.080 --> 21:29.920
You look so [Laughs]
different.

21:29.920 --> 21:32.330
You look...great.

21:32.330 --> 21:33.500
You look great.

21:33.500 --> 21:34.880
What are you doing
in town?

21:34.880 --> 21:37.040
Uh, just visiting
the fam.

21:37.040 --> 21:38.500
Oh, your niece
is such a good kid --

21:38.500 --> 21:39.880
one of my favorite
students.

21:39.880 --> 21:42.040
Oh, you're back here
teaching?

21:42.040 --> 21:44.330
Believe it or not.
History.

21:44.330 --> 21:45.880
[ Laughing ]
I mean, sometimes I feel like

21:45.880 --> 21:47.000
I never graduated.

21:47.000 --> 21:48.880
Hmm.
[ Sighs ]

21:48.880 --> 21:50.040
It's really good
that you're here.

21:50.040 --> 21:51.210
Reese, you know,
she's just --

21:51.210 --> 21:52.460
She's been through
so much.

21:52.460 --> 21:53.460
Yeah.
I've been --

21:53.460 --> 21:55.170
I've been trying
to make time for her

21:55.170 --> 21:57.330
and pull her
out of her shell.

21:57.330 --> 21:59.000
So, what's, uh --
What's going on with you?

21:59.000 --> 22:01.920
You, uh...
married or anything?

22:01.920 --> 22:03.000
Are you serious?!
Oh!

22:03.000 --> 22:04.540
Still single.
[ Coughs ]

22:04.540 --> 22:05.920
Work keeps me busy,
so...

22:05.920 --> 22:07.670
Mm.
How 'bout you?

22:07.670 --> 22:10.290
I-I heard you're a big
financial investor in New York?

22:10.290 --> 22:11.790
Oh. Uh...

22:11.790 --> 22:13.880
You think now is a good time
to hit on your ex?

22:13.880 --> 22:15.000
Is that what's happening?

22:15.000 --> 22:16.120
What about Reese?
Um...

22:16.120 --> 22:17.500
Yeah.

22:17.500 --> 22:19.000
Well, I sort of
got out of that business.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.790
I'm just trying
something different.

22:20.790 --> 22:22.290
Wow. I-- I'm surprised,

22:22.290 --> 22:23.710
'cause, you know,
you were always that guy

22:23.710 --> 22:25.120
who was gonna be billionaire
by the time he was 30.

22:25.120 --> 22:27.330
Yeah, well, um...

22:27.330 --> 22:28.420
my, uh --
We have work to do,
Kevin.

22:28.420 --> 22:29.880
My priorities
have shifted.
Oh.

22:29.880 --> 22:31.500
We have to start now.
Um...
there -- there's, uh --

22:31.500 --> 22:32.920
There's more important things
than, uh...
So say goodbye.

22:32.920 --> 22:34.750
...than money.
Goodbye.

22:34.750 --> 22:36.330
Sure. Well, I hope you find
something that makes you happy.

22:36.330 --> 22:37.290
Goodbye!

22:37.290 --> 22:39.040
Okay. Goodbye. Goodbye.

22:39.040 --> 22:40.580
There it is.
Come on, now.

22:40.580 --> 22:41.920
Oh. Bye.

22:41.920 --> 22:43.120
I said "Goodbye"!

22:43.120 --> 22:44.380
No, I know. I wasn't --
I know. Not --

22:44.380 --> 22:45.250
I didn't --
I wasn't...

22:45.250 --> 22:46.250
Okay, bye.
Just -- Yeah.

22:46.250 --> 22:47.290
Goodbye.
Yeah.

22:47.290 --> 22:51.540
♪♪

22:51.540 --> 22:52.790
[ Whistle blows in distance,
indistinct conversations ]

22:52.790 --> 22:54.960
[ Ball bounces ]

22:57.330 --> 22:59.120
My mother talked to you.

23:01.290 --> 23:02.880
Let's kick the ball around.

23:02.880 --> 23:04.210
Kevin: Here's the deal.

23:04.210 --> 23:05.500
If I score on you,

23:05.500 --> 23:06.880
you don't
have to do anything --

23:06.880 --> 23:09.000
no soccer,
no extracurricular activities.

23:09.000 --> 23:10.460
You just stay home,

23:10.460 --> 23:11.620
listen to My Chemical Romance,

23:11.620 --> 23:13.040
and wear
all the black clothes.

23:13.040 --> 23:15.170
But if you make the save,

23:15.170 --> 23:17.500
then you have to play
soccer.

23:17.500 --> 23:19.290
This is dumb.

23:19.290 --> 23:21.710
Well, any answer but no
means yes.

23:21.710 --> 23:24.460
Get ready for the heat!

23:26.380 --> 23:28.670
Aha!

23:28.670 --> 23:30.500
You scored.
I don't have to play.

23:30.500 --> 23:31.620
Are we done now?

23:32.620 --> 23:34.000
Wait, wait.

23:34.000 --> 23:34.960
Uh, no,
I made a mistake.

23:34.960 --> 23:36.330
I-I screwed up the rules.

23:36.330 --> 23:38.080
Um, do over.

23:38.080 --> 23:39.380
Do over!

23:39.380 --> 23:41.040
If I score,
then you have to play,

23:41.040 --> 23:42.120
so give me the ball.

23:45.170 --> 23:46.750
You think you can just
come into our lives

23:46.750 --> 23:47.830
and fix everything?

23:47.830 --> 23:49.710
I don't even know you.

23:49.710 --> 23:52.040
You're a Christmas card
with 20 bucks in it.

23:52.040 --> 23:53.580
[ Whistle blows
in distance ]

23:53.580 --> 23:56.750
I mean, $50.

23:56.750 --> 23:58.750
You were late
to my dad's funeral,

23:58.750 --> 24:00.000
and you left early.

24:00.000 --> 24:02.880
♪♪

24:02.880 --> 24:04.960
I...I did do that.

24:04.960 --> 24:06.710
And we haven't even seen you
since then,

24:06.710 --> 24:08.170
and that was, what,
18 months ago?

24:08.170 --> 24:10.540
You want to know
what you missed?

24:10.540 --> 24:12.920
My mom in bed
for two weeks straight.

24:12.920 --> 24:14.920
She's still crazy about you.

24:14.920 --> 24:16.040
I have no idea why.

24:16.040 --> 24:19.000
Look, I...[ Scoffs ]

24:19.000 --> 24:20.040
I suck.

24:20.040 --> 24:22.830
I mean, I-I absolutely do.

24:22.830 --> 24:26.080
But, um...

24:26.080 --> 24:28.000
I'm here now.

24:28.000 --> 24:30.620
You're here because you have
nowhere else to go.

24:30.620 --> 24:38.920
♪♪

24:38.920 --> 24:41.710
♪♪

24:41.710 --> 24:43.460
Yvette: All right.

24:43.460 --> 24:45.500
Maybe helping Reese out of gate
wasn't the best idea.

24:45.500 --> 24:48.330
I thought if I threw you
in the deep end, you'd swim.

24:48.330 --> 24:50.080
I made a mistake.
I can own that.

24:50.080 --> 24:51.540
♪ Keep my hands to myself ♪

24:51.540 --> 24:53.960
Look, I thought you had
more aptitude for this.

24:53.960 --> 24:55.920
Turns out,
you are fairly incompetent.

24:55.920 --> 24:57.250
No,
I think it went great.

24:57.250 --> 24:58.670
This'll be good.

24:58.670 --> 25:00.960
Good for what?

25:00.960 --> 25:04.380
Training.

25:04.380 --> 25:06.920
The only job you have in life
for the foreseeable future

25:06.920 --> 25:09.290
is to build up
your spiritual powers

25:09.290 --> 25:11.790
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

25:11.790 --> 25:13.290
Now, after you've done so,

25:13.290 --> 25:14.330
God is gonna show you

25:14.330 --> 25:16.040
how to find
the other righteous,

25:16.040 --> 25:18.710
and then you'll anoint them
with an embrace.

25:18.710 --> 25:21.670
A hug?
Yep.

25:21.670 --> 25:24.620
So I'm supposed to go around
hugging strangers.

25:24.620 --> 25:27.040
Should I just register
as a sex offender now,

25:27.040 --> 25:28.540
or...?

25:28.540 --> 25:29.750
You -- you --

25:29.750 --> 25:31.750
you know
what a hug is, right?

25:31.750 --> 25:33.620
Oh, and --
and one more thing,

25:33.620 --> 25:35.540
and this is
really important --

25:35.540 --> 25:38.250
You can never tell anyone
that you're one of the 36.

25:38.250 --> 25:40.000
Why not?

25:40.000 --> 25:41.580
I don't make the rules.

25:41.580 --> 25:43.040
♪ I'm a rebel
just for kicks now ♪
Face this way.

25:43.040 --> 25:44.620
♪ I've been feeling it
since 1966, now ♪

25:44.620 --> 25:46.620
You've spent your life
focused on things

25:46.620 --> 25:47.830
that don't really matter

25:47.830 --> 25:50.040
like money, power, sex,
external appearance,

25:50.040 --> 25:52.000
but none of that's
made you happy.

25:52.000 --> 25:54.580
So once you let go of
all the superficial trappings,

25:54.580 --> 25:56.960
you'll feel a peace
that you've never known.

25:56.960 --> 25:58.920
Okay.
That sounds pretty good.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.750
Now inhale.

26:00.750 --> 26:01.920
[ Both inhaling sharply ]

26:01.920 --> 26:02.830
And exhale.

26:02.830 --> 26:04.420
[ Both exhaling sharply ]

26:04.420 --> 26:06.540
And let go over
everything in your life

26:06.540 --> 26:09.000
that has no spiritual value.

26:09.000 --> 26:10.750
♪ Give in to that easy living,
goodbye to my hopes and dreams ♪

26:10.750 --> 26:13.830
[ Exhales sharply ]

26:13.830 --> 26:16.080
[ Engine revs ]

26:16.080 --> 26:19.500
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

26:19.500 --> 26:22.620
♪ Let me kick it
like it's 1986 now ♪

26:22.620 --> 26:24.250
♪ Might be over now ♪

26:24.250 --> 26:25.880
Great.
♪ But I feel it still ♪

26:25.880 --> 26:27.080
Lesson over.
♪ Might've had your fill ♪

26:27.080 --> 26:28.120
♪ But you feel it still ♪

26:31.750 --> 26:35.500
♪♪

26:35.500 --> 26:38.330
Purcell: Well, I think
we're done here, Kevin.

26:38.330 --> 26:39.920
I'm gonna write this up
as no liability.

26:39.920 --> 26:41.540
Charlie feels awful.

26:41.540 --> 26:44.210
Well, it's not his fault.

26:44.210 --> 26:45.880
We all know
whose fault it is!

26:47.250 --> 26:49.830
All right, then.

26:49.830 --> 26:50.710
How's your sister doing?

26:50.710 --> 26:52.420
She's okay.

26:52.420 --> 26:53.580
Oh, wait.

26:53.580 --> 26:54.710
You had a thing for her
in high school,

26:54.710 --> 26:55.880
didn't you?

26:55.880 --> 26:58.710
♪♪

26:58.710 --> 26:59.920
[ Exhales ]

26:59.920 --> 27:01.080
You're free to go.

27:01.080 --> 27:02.040
Give that
to your insurance.

27:03.380 --> 27:04.880
I check in on them
from time to time,

27:04.880 --> 27:06.250
make sure
they're doing all right.

27:06.250 --> 27:07.920
That's really cool, Nate.
Thanks.

27:14.000 --> 27:15.790
I guess you need
a lift home.

27:15.790 --> 27:16.880
Oh, that'd be great.

27:16.880 --> 27:18.210
You have to ride in the back.

27:18.210 --> 27:28.210
♪♪

27:28.210 --> 27:31.170
♪♪

27:31.170 --> 27:33.790
Kevin: Hey.

27:33.790 --> 27:36.000
You're back. [ Laughs ]

27:36.000 --> 27:38.830
What's, uh --
What's going on?

27:38.830 --> 27:40.830
Well,
Ms. Allen was kind enough

27:40.830 --> 27:43.580
to bring Reese home
from school today.

27:43.580 --> 27:45.000
At least somebody around here
is responsible.

27:45.000 --> 27:46.250
Yeah. Cool.

27:46.250 --> 27:47.670
Oh, it's, you know,
no problem.

27:47.670 --> 27:49.710
Anytime.

27:49.710 --> 27:50.830
Thanks. Heh.

27:50.830 --> 27:52.790
So, I-I have to --
I'm gonna -- This was --

27:52.790 --> 27:53.960
Oh.
Yeah.

27:53.960 --> 27:55.040
Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

27:56.830 --> 27:57.540
Bye!
Bye --

27:57.540 --> 27:59.120
Okay...

28:04.830 --> 28:05.830
[ Engine starts
in distance ]

28:05.830 --> 28:07.120
So, the helicopter,
that was --

28:07.120 --> 28:09.040
Did you go
to the meteor site?

28:09.040 --> 28:11.710
Um...

28:12.580 --> 28:13.920
Well, here's the thing --
No, no, no.

28:13.920 --> 28:15.120
I already talked to Reese.

28:15.120 --> 28:16.830
I want to know
what the hell's going on, okay,

28:16.830 --> 28:18.250
and I don't want any jokes,

28:18.250 --> 28:19.790
and I don't want
any of your usual garbage.

28:19.790 --> 28:20.790
Ame, come on.

28:20.790 --> 28:22.040
Tell me the truth.

28:23.830 --> 28:24.960
W-We did, yes.

28:24.960 --> 28:26.580
But it was my idea.

28:26.580 --> 28:28.040
It was my own,
personal idea.

28:28.040 --> 28:29.500
I can't even believe

28:29.500 --> 28:32.460
that I'm asking you
this question, but...

28:32.460 --> 28:33.790
what did you do
with the meteorite?

28:33.790 --> 28:34.540
[ Inhales sharply ]

28:34.540 --> 28:37.580
Ohh. Um...

28:37.580 --> 28:38.670
Oh...

28:38.670 --> 28:40.420
I -- um, yeah --

28:40.420 --> 28:42.290
not really allowed
to, uh, talk --

28:42.290 --> 28:44.040
You're lying!
No, no, no, no, no.
It's --

28:44.040 --> 28:45.460
Kevin, you're putting
my daughter in jeopardy.

28:45.460 --> 28:46.330
This isn't a joke!

28:46.330 --> 28:47.580
Um --

28:47.580 --> 28:48.670
Okay, all right. Fine.

28:48.670 --> 28:50.540
Sit down, sit down.
Please.

28:50.540 --> 28:53.120
[ Sighs ]
Um...

28:54.710 --> 28:57.830
Okay, I-I-I'm going to
tell you something,

28:57.830 --> 29:00.380
and it's going to sound...
insane,

29:00.380 --> 29:02.620
uh, legitimately crazy.

29:02.620 --> 29:04.880
But you know how
we have that twin thing

29:04.880 --> 29:06.960
where we can
read each other's minds?

29:06.960 --> 29:08.290
We don't have that.

29:08.290 --> 29:09.380
Yes, we do.

29:09.380 --> 29:10.330
You can always tell
when I'm lying.

29:10.330 --> 29:12.000
Because you're not
a good liar.

29:14.420 --> 29:16.790
Well, that is
very disappointing to me.

29:16.790 --> 29:19.750
[ Scoffs ]
Um, all right.

29:19.750 --> 29:22.830
The truth is...

29:22.830 --> 29:24.330
when we were
in eighth grade,

29:24.330 --> 29:25.880
I sold your underwear
to Mikey DeFalco.

29:25.880 --> 29:27.210
♪♪

29:27.210 --> 29:28.830
Damn it, Kevin.
W-- Wait.

29:28.830 --> 29:30.080
What did I just say?

29:30.080 --> 29:32.500
Do you like
doing this to people?

29:32.500 --> 29:34.500
No, no, no, no, no.
Do you --

29:34.500 --> 29:36.170
Do you like making people feel
stupid for trusting you?

29:36.170 --> 29:38.330
No, no, no.
Wait, wait, wait.

29:38.330 --> 29:40.420
Hold on.
All right, all right.

29:40.420 --> 29:41.920
[ Exhales sharply,
clears throat ]

29:43.120 --> 29:45.710
Sophomore year
I stole your band camp money --

29:45.710 --> 29:47.040
To buy weed.

29:47.040 --> 29:48.540
No!
I can't believe this.

29:48.540 --> 29:49.880
Gah! What did I just say?!

29:49.880 --> 29:52.170
I can't -- I can't believe
that you turned into this.

29:52.170 --> 29:55.120
♪♪

29:55.120 --> 29:56.040
Okay.

29:57.500 --> 29:59.500
Okay.

29:59.500 --> 30:00.710
♪♪

30:00.710 --> 30:02.540
Take a look at that.

30:02.540 --> 30:04.750
♪♪

30:04.750 --> 30:05.790
"I slept with
Connie Boccabella

30:05.790 --> 30:07.000
at your wedding"?

30:07.000 --> 30:08.500
What?
Seriously, Kevin,

30:08.500 --> 30:09.710
you're the worst person
I know.

30:09.710 --> 30:10.710
I wrote that?

30:10.710 --> 30:12.080
No, that --

30:12.080 --> 30:15.420
♪♪

30:15.420 --> 30:19.120
Kevin, you and Reese
are all that I have left.

30:21.830 --> 30:23.040
I -- [ Sighs ]

30:23.040 --> 30:25.040
When you did
what you did,

30:25.040 --> 30:27.920
when you tried
to end your life,

30:27.920 --> 30:29.000
that almost killed me.

30:31.210 --> 30:32.790
Because it meant
that you didn't care.

30:32.790 --> 30:34.620
No, no, no. Amy --

30:34.620 --> 30:37.080
Amy, that is not true.
Kevin...

30:37.080 --> 30:39.500
I can't be the only person

30:39.500 --> 30:42.500
that cares about this
relationship anymore.

30:42.500 --> 30:43.620
I can't.

30:43.620 --> 30:45.540
I can't have that
around me.

30:45.540 --> 30:47.000
I just --

30:47.000 --> 30:48.380
I can't have that
around Reese.

30:50.830 --> 30:54.000
Kevin, I love you.

30:56.580 --> 30:58.750
I know.
We're a part
of each other.

30:58.750 --> 31:01.960
[ Sighs ]

31:01.960 --> 31:04.000
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:04.000 --> 31:05.620
But if you're gonna be
like this, I just --

31:05.620 --> 31:09.080
Uh, I...

31:09.080 --> 31:11.040
I'll go. I'll --
No, that's not
what I'm saying.

31:11.040 --> 31:12.420
I --
Y-Yeah, yeah, you are.

31:12.420 --> 31:22.420
♪♪

31:22.420 --> 31:27.420
♪♪

31:27.420 --> 31:28.830
Hey. Um...

31:28.830 --> 31:29.880
[ Clicks tongue ]

31:31.830 --> 31:33.830
So, I'm gonna go.

31:33.830 --> 31:35.380
My mom made me tell her.

31:35.380 --> 31:37.960
Oh. Yeah, don't even...

31:37.960 --> 31:40.330
That's not your job
to lie for me.

31:40.330 --> 31:41.620
Um...

31:41.620 --> 31:43.040
Oh, but for
what it's worth,

31:43.040 --> 31:44.670
she's not gonna give up
on, uh, soccer.

31:44.670 --> 31:46.880
So my advice would be

31:46.880 --> 31:48.960
to just find a thing
and do it

31:48.960 --> 31:50.830
so she'll calm down.

31:50.830 --> 31:52.290
Uh, bye, Reese.

31:53.920 --> 31:56.380
Uh, that's --
All right.

32:04.120 --> 32:06.580
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

32:06.580 --> 32:09.330
[ Sighs ]

32:09.330 --> 32:10.710
Yeah?

32:10.710 --> 32:13.040
Dr. Sloane:
Kevin, it's Dr. Sloane.

32:13.040 --> 32:14.710
My office said
you were in crisis.

32:14.710 --> 32:15.540
What's going on?

32:17.420 --> 32:20.000
Um...[ Sighs ]

32:20.000 --> 32:22.420
Oh, I thought
I was hallucinating.

32:22.420 --> 32:26.920
But then I thought
that I wasn't.

32:26.920 --> 32:28.210
I don't know.

32:28.210 --> 32:30.580
Maybe -- maybe
none of it was real.

32:30.580 --> 32:32.120
Uh...

32:32.120 --> 32:34.500
[ Chuckles ]

32:34.500 --> 32:36.830
♪♪

32:36.830 --> 32:38.830
Dr. Sloane?

32:38.830 --> 32:40.170
[ Clicks tongue ]
Are you still there?

32:40.170 --> 32:42.040
[ Inhales sharply ]
Great.

32:42.420 --> 32:43.790
Ow!

32:43.790 --> 32:45.540
Am I real enough
for you now?!
Aah!

32:45.540 --> 32:47.620
Am I real for you,
Kevin?!

32:47.620 --> 32:48.790
What is wrong with you?

32:48.790 --> 32:49.830
What's wrong with me?

32:49.830 --> 32:51.460
What is wrong with you?
[ Sighs ]

32:51.460 --> 32:53.500
Do you understand
what's at stake here?

32:53.500 --> 32:56.120
The world is not gonna end
if I go home.

32:56.120 --> 32:58.290
There are worse things than
the end of the world,

32:58.290 --> 32:59.880
but you already know that,
Kevin.

32:59.880 --> 33:01.500
Think about how you felt

33:01.500 --> 33:03.750
when you tried
to take your own life.

33:03.750 --> 33:05.790
Now imagine
the whole of humanity

33:05.790 --> 33:07.080
feeling that way.

33:07.080 --> 33:09.790
That is what the world faces
without the righteous.

33:09.790 --> 33:12.210
I think that
you should just go back

33:12.210 --> 33:14.500
to wherever it is
that you came from,

33:14.500 --> 33:16.920
'cause I'm done
with all of this and with you.

33:16.920 --> 33:17.710
I can't.
[ Bag jostles ]

33:17.710 --> 33:18.960
[ Sighs ]

33:18.960 --> 33:21.330
Can't what?
Go back.

33:21.330 --> 33:23.710
Coming here
was a one-way ticket.

33:23.710 --> 33:25.330
♪♪

33:25.330 --> 33:27.330
I gave up paradise
for you.

33:27.330 --> 33:29.000
Wh--

33:29.000 --> 33:30.620
[ Sighs ]

33:30.620 --> 33:37.500
♪♪

33:41.040 --> 33:42.710
Woman #1: Vendor Airlines,
flight 174

33:42.710 --> 33:44.210
is now boarding at gate --
Woman #2: Transform yourself.

33:46.500 --> 33:50.040
♪♪

33:50.040 --> 33:51.920
Transform yourself.

33:51.920 --> 33:58.330
♪♪

33:58.330 --> 34:00.250
Transform yourself --

34:00.250 --> 34:02.920
Confidence, beauty, renewal.

34:02.920 --> 34:05.790
Englestein
Plastic Surgery Center.

34:05.790 --> 34:09.670
Transform yourself
into something new.

34:13.040 --> 34:17.880
♪♪

34:17.880 --> 34:20.460
Call now for
your free consultation.

34:20.460 --> 34:22.170
Transform yourself.
Kevin: Sir!

34:23.250 --> 34:25.040
♪♪

34:25.040 --> 34:27.540
Sir? Hey! Sir!

34:27.540 --> 34:33.830
♪♪

34:33.830 --> 34:36.250
Reese: Kevin! Kevin!

34:36.250 --> 34:38.170
Reese? What are y--

34:38.170 --> 34:39.170
How did you get past
security?

34:39.170 --> 34:40.080
I used my mom's miles.

34:40.080 --> 34:43.580
I-- I mean --
Well, did you ask her?

34:43.580 --> 34:45.210
So, you're just
gonna leave?
No --

34:45.210 --> 34:46.290
Just walk away
from your family

34:46.290 --> 34:47.580
and think
that's totally fine?

34:47.580 --> 34:49.170
Can we talk about this
later?

34:49.170 --> 34:50.460
You can't do that
to my mom!

34:50.460 --> 34:52.500
You can't just drop in
and blow up her life,

34:52.500 --> 34:54.670
and what are you even
looking for?
Uh -- uh --

34:54.670 --> 34:56.040
I'm about to do
something weird.

34:56.040 --> 34:57.580
You only ever do
weird things.

34:57.580 --> 34:58.380
Kevin --

35:00.790 --> 35:02.210
Hi! Sorry.

35:02.210 --> 35:03.960
I'm, uh -- I'm Kevin.

35:03.960 --> 35:05.040
Sorry to -- to bother you.

35:05.040 --> 35:06.710
I know this sounds crazy,

35:06.710 --> 35:08.670
but I feel like
I'm supposed to...

35:08.670 --> 35:10.250
Or like...

35:13.750 --> 35:14.960
[ Laughs ]

35:14.960 --> 35:16.580
Uh...

35:20.710 --> 35:23.420
Sorry. Um...

35:23.420 --> 35:26.620
Three weeks ago,
I-I took a bunch of pills,

35:26.620 --> 35:29.540
and I tried to kill
myself.

35:29.540 --> 35:32.500
Uh, I-I'd just got fired,
and my girlfriend left me,

35:32.500 --> 35:33.960
and [Clears throat] --

35:33.960 --> 35:37.620
I-I don't know
if I ever really loved her,

35:37.620 --> 35:41.040
and I neglected

35:41.040 --> 35:44.710
the most important relationship
of my life,

35:44.710 --> 35:48.710
my amazing, crazy sister

35:48.710 --> 35:50.790
who all she ever did
was love me,

35:50.790 --> 35:53.750
and every time I talked to her,
I felt guilty about it,

35:53.750 --> 35:56.080
so I just stopped
talking to her.

35:56.080 --> 35:58.880
♪♪

35:58.880 --> 36:05.290
I'm not a good person.

36:05.290 --> 36:07.620
But, um...

36:07.620 --> 36:11.120
something has changed.

36:11.120 --> 36:16.210
And I feel like
maybe there's a point.

36:16.210 --> 36:17.460
Maybe there's --

36:17.460 --> 36:19.210
there's something
to live for.

36:19.210 --> 36:22.000
and I'm -- I'm --

36:22.000 --> 36:24.000
I'm getting
a second chance.

36:24.000 --> 36:27.210
And I can't explain why,

36:27.210 --> 36:29.330
but you're a part of that.

36:29.330 --> 36:31.580
So, um...

36:31.580 --> 36:35.120
if you don't mind, can I --
can I hug you?

36:35.120 --> 36:36.920
Quick hug,
no weird stuff.

36:36.920 --> 36:38.290
Is that okay?
Just a --

36:39.920 --> 36:41.580
[ Bag unzips ]

36:41.580 --> 36:50.710
♪♪

36:50.710 --> 36:53.880
[ Chuckles ]

36:53.880 --> 36:55.380
Ah...[ Laughs ]

36:55.380 --> 36:56.420
That is perfect.

36:56.420 --> 36:57.830
[ Sniffles ]

36:57.830 --> 37:03.040
That's the perfect end
to this stupid trip.

37:05.620 --> 37:06.830
Oh, yeah, yeah.

37:06.830 --> 37:08.080
Yes, I'll, uh --

37:08.080 --> 37:10.120
I'll buy your --
your pencil.

37:13.210 --> 37:15.000
Actually,
you know what?

37:15.000 --> 37:16.830
Just take it all.

37:16.830 --> 37:18.670
Sorry to bother you.

37:24.380 --> 37:34.380
♪♪

37:34.380 --> 37:44.330
♪♪

37:44.330 --> 37:54.380
♪♪

37:54.380 --> 37:57.880
♪♪

37:57.880 --> 37:59.670
What was that?
What just happened?

37:59.670 --> 38:02.580
Woman: 13, passenger Stanley,
please report to Gate...

38:02.580 --> 38:07.000
That guy...

38:07.000 --> 38:08.960
was wearing
so much Drakkar Noir.

38:08.960 --> 38:10.080
You're a jerk!

38:10.080 --> 38:11.960
Reese, it was a ton.

38:11.960 --> 38:14.750
I can taste it.

38:14.750 --> 38:17.250
So what happened?

38:17.250 --> 38:18.040
I just...

38:19.920 --> 38:22.670
I understand now.

38:22.670 --> 38:29.120
♪♪

38:29.120 --> 38:32.170
Kevin:
Look, I just want to know

38:32.170 --> 38:36.540
if Kristin said anything
about me.

38:36.540 --> 38:38.620
Reese: I'm not talking about
Miss Allen with you.

38:38.620 --> 38:40.620
[ Sighs ]

38:40.620 --> 38:41.670
All right, well, then,

38:41.670 --> 38:43.080
how 'bout
a little light stalking?

38:43.080 --> 38:44.540
No!
You'd do that.

38:44.540 --> 38:46.880
Come on.
Stop asking.

38:47.210 --> 38:48.830
Oh, hey.

38:48.830 --> 38:49.880
Heads up.

39:01.710 --> 39:02.710
You all right?

39:04.420 --> 39:09.380
My dad and I had this ritual
after soccer practice.

39:09.380 --> 39:10.830
He told me if I can find
enough loose change

39:10.830 --> 39:12.000
rolling around his car,

39:12.000 --> 39:13.290
we could stop
for ice cream.

39:13.290 --> 39:17.790
So I'd dig around the floor,
in between the seats,

39:17.790 --> 39:18.880
and I'd always find

39:18.880 --> 39:20.500
just enough money I needed
for ice cream.

39:20.500 --> 39:22.250
Even when I figured out

39:22.250 --> 39:24.120
he was just
putting the money there,

39:24.120 --> 39:25.290
I never said anything.

39:25.290 --> 39:26.960
He never said anything.

39:30.880 --> 39:32.750
Soccer was something
we did together.

39:32.750 --> 39:34.790
It was our thing.
It was never my thing.

39:34.790 --> 39:38.000
So I just don't want to play
anymore.

39:38.000 --> 39:39.920
Okay.

39:39.920 --> 39:41.460
Then don't.

39:41.460 --> 39:43.790
♪♪

39:43.790 --> 39:47.580
And I was thinking about
what you said.

39:47.580 --> 39:49.170
And...

39:49.170 --> 39:50.290
I don't know,
there's play tryouts

39:50.290 --> 39:51.380
at school next week,

39:51.380 --> 39:52.540
so maybe I'll do that.

39:52.540 --> 39:54.750
♪♪

39:54.750 --> 39:56.330
Theater nerd? Ugh.

39:56.330 --> 39:57.460
I mean, I guess.
Shut up!

39:57.460 --> 39:58.670
[ Groans ]

39:58.670 --> 40:01.710
I don't have to go see
any of your plays, do I?

40:01.710 --> 40:03.540
Everything about you
is bad.

40:03.540 --> 40:05.750
[ Scoffs ]

40:05.750 --> 40:07.330
I'm doing homework.

40:07.330 --> 40:08.620
Amy: All right.

40:10.500 --> 40:12.210
Uh, hi.

40:12.210 --> 40:14.580
So...

40:14.580 --> 40:16.170
Listen, um --

40:16.170 --> 40:20.250
♪♪

40:20.250 --> 40:22.170
I mean,
I had a whole speech planned.

40:22.170 --> 40:23.790
[ Chuckles ]

40:23.790 --> 40:27.250
♪♪

40:27.250 --> 40:29.580
Have you been here
this whole time?

40:29.580 --> 40:31.620
No, I've been in conference
with my colleagues.

40:31.620 --> 40:32.710
You have colleagues?

40:32.710 --> 40:33.710
Hmm -- 36 meteors?

40:33.710 --> 40:34.710
I'm not the only one
who came here.

40:34.710 --> 40:36.920
I found one.

40:36.920 --> 40:38.620
At the airport.

40:38.620 --> 40:41.170
I-I don't even know
how to describe it.

40:41.170 --> 40:43.620
It was -- It was like
for one brief moment,

40:43.620 --> 40:48.460
I understood the Universe
and my place within it.

40:48.460 --> 40:50.830
Ooh, Kevin!

40:50.830 --> 40:52.830
That's beautiful!
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

40:52.830 --> 40:54.210
He wasn't
one of the righteous.

40:56.580 --> 40:57.580
The hell
are you talking about?

40:57.580 --> 40:59.000
Sorry.

40:59.000 --> 41:01.670
No, that doesn't --
I-I had feelings!

41:01.670 --> 41:03.880
I had a bunch of feelings.

41:03.880 --> 41:05.330
I'm really proud of you,

41:05.330 --> 41:06.540
but it's not gonna be
that easy.

41:06.540 --> 41:09.120
There was, like...

41:09.120 --> 41:10.120
[ Sighs ]

41:12.500 --> 41:19.790
♪♪

41:19.790 --> 41:21.920
Did you see that?

41:21.920 --> 41:23.170
See what?

41:23.170 --> 41:26.540
It was butterflies,
I think.

41:26.540 --> 41:28.880
I don't know.
[ Gasps ] It's a sign.

41:28.880 --> 41:31.170
It's a sign! [ Laughs ]
[ Laughs nervously ]

41:31.170 --> 41:33.080
You're on the right path.

41:33.080 --> 41:35.080
But what does that mean?

41:35.080 --> 41:37.210
Uh, just -- just keep doing
what you're doing.

41:37.210 --> 41:38.920
The Universe
will make the rest clear.

41:38.920 --> 41:40.960
Okay?
You need to get to bed early.

41:40.960 --> 41:43.080
Tomorrow's when
the real training starts.

41:43.080 --> 41:44.540
Oh, cool.

41:44.540 --> 41:47.080
I look forward to you destroying
some more of my stuff.

41:47.080 --> 41:48.670
Oh, now come on!

41:48.670 --> 41:51.460
You know I have to tear you down
to build you up!

41:51.460 --> 41:53.380
Well, maybe you could, uh,

41:53.380 --> 41:55.250
build me up a car
while you're at it.

41:55.250 --> 41:57.290
A Tesla would be nice,
but you know what I like.

41:57.290 --> 42:00.500
Reese:
Maybe he isn't crazy.

42:00.500 --> 42:03.000
Well, how am I
supposed to get around?

42:03.000 --> 42:05.170
Maybe it's possible

42:05.170 --> 42:07.380
that one person can actually
make a difference.

42:07.380 --> 42:09.830
It's like
he's gotten a second chance,

42:09.830 --> 42:12.750
and he's using it to do
something important.

42:12.750 --> 42:14.170
[ Laughs ] Oh, yeah!
All right.

42:14.170 --> 42:18.420
Look, I just want to know
if you can fly.

42:18.420 --> 42:20.790
I think it's a totally
reasonable question.

42:20.790 --> 42:23.580
Except, yeah,
he's super crazy.

42:23.580 --> 42:27.290
Do you, like, zip around,
or can you, like --

42:27.290 --> 42:28.290
Do you just have wings?
Just tell me.

42:30.920 --> 42:40.920
♪♪

42:40.920 --> 42:50.960
♪♪

42:50.960 --> 42:59.330
♪♪
